{
  "texts": [
    "In the postoperative complication prediction task, the F 1 -score of methods using KNN exceeded the average of the 3 clinicians, although 1 clinician achieved the best accuracy when dropping a high recall value.",
    "In all 6 KNN methods, introducing the indicator combination ratio and distinguishing the primary diagnosis in the similarity measurement can truly improve the overall performance of the F 1 -score.",
    "LR models constructed using the KNN-obtained patient groups were able to generally achieve better predictions compared to simple voting of similar patients and the LR model based on k random patients.",
    "Interestingly, both the model with the best F 1 -score performance and the model with the best AUC used the original values.",
    "This may be because original values are more reflective of individualized patient differences in a similar patient population."
  ]
}